FixedRotHelp
                                                  01
   FIXED AXIS OF ROTATION                         02
                                                  03
The object is constrained to rotate about a fixed 04
axis specified by the omega vector.  This axis    05
and the initial orientation of the object can     06
be changed by selecting "Initial Conditions" under07
the "parameters" menu.                            08
                                                  09
Note that a torque will be usually be required to 10
keep the rotation axis fixed, so the angular      11
momentum will not be conserved.  Nor will it be   12
parallel to then angular velocity.                13
                                                  14
The moment of inertia of the object may be changed15
by selecting "Moment of Inertia" under the        16
"Parameters" menu.                                17
                                                  18
Select a new system by choosing "Systems"         19
