FixedTorHelp
                FIXED TORQUE                      01
                                                  02
The object is free to rotate about its center of  03
mass with a fixed torque applied.                 04
                                                  05
When the torque is set to zero, the angular       06
momentum will be conserved.  The angular velocity 07
will not, however, in general be conserved.       08
The initial angular velocity can be changed by    09
selecting "Initial Conditions" under the          10
"Parameters" menu.                                11
                                                  12
The moment of inertia of the object may be changed13
by selecting "Moment of Inertia" under the        14
"Parameters" menu.                                15
