SpinTopHelp
               SPINNING TOP                       01
                                                  02
In this system the torque applied to the object   03
about its center of mass is given by              04
    Torque = T0 sin(theta)                        05
where theta is the Euler angle representing the   06
angle between the z and z' axes.                  07
                                                  08
The default parameters for this system cause the  09
object to precess with its z axis nearly          10
constrained to the x-y plane.  You can change the 11
initial orientation and the angular velocity by   12
selecting "Initial Conditions" under the          13
"Parameters" menu.                                14
                                                  15
The moment of inertia of the object may be changed16
by selecting "Moment of Inertia" under the        17
"Parameters" menu.                                18
                                                  19
Select a new system by choosing "Systems".        20
