GetInitCondHelp
Coordinates 0.36 0.3
         GET INITIAL CONDITIONS                   01
The orientations of the object, the initial       02
angular velocity and the initial torque (if the   03
problem has an initial torque) are all given in   04
Euler angles:                                     05
  -Theta is identical to the theta of spherical   06
   coordinates                                    07
  -Phi is similar to the phi of spherical         08
   coordinates except that it is the angle        09
   from the negative y axis.                      10
  -Psi is the angle of rotation about the axis    11
   specified by Theta and Psi.                    12
                                                  13
Note that input for omega and torque do not       14
include an angle Psi since this rotation is       15
meaningless for a vector.                         16
