          CHANGE DISPLAYS                         01
                                                  02
The rotation may also be shown from the body      03
frame by selecting Body-Centered Frame.           04
                                                  05
Select which objects you wish displayed on each   06
graph.  Note that selecting Torque will always    07
select angular momentum since Torque is displayed 08
relative to the angular momentum to emphasize the 09
fact that dL/dt = Torque.                         10
                                                  11
Change scales if some vectors are too large or    12
too small.                                        13
                                                  14
            STEREO-GRAPHIC IMAGING                15
Selecting StereoGraphic causes two images to be   16
drawn of each screen.  To see the 3-D image, sit  17
back from the screen about 3 feet and focus at a  18
point behind the screen to bring the two separate 19
images together at the center.  You will see three20
images, but concentrate on the middle image only. 21
This is easier when the animation is running.     22
If you display the body centered frame as well,   23
the graphs are smaller and stereographic imaging  24
is easier.                                        25

ChangeObjectDimensionsHelp
Coordinates 0.0 0.3
          CHANGE MOMENT OF INERTIA                01
                                                  02
Adjust the dimension of the object by clicking    03
the mouse on the slider.  If you click on the     04
slider arrows the slider moves incrementally.     05
If you click in the bar the slider jumps by a     06
larger amount.  You may also click and drag the   07
slider itself for faster change.  From the        08
keyboard you may move between sliders with the    09
tab key and move the slider with the arrow key.   10
                                                  11
The moment of inertia is calculated by assuming   12
that the object consists of 8 point masses at the 13
corners of the rectangular wire-frame.            14
