GetNumericalParametersHelp
             NUMERICAL PARAMETERS                 01
                                                  02
The value entered here for dtAnim will be the     03
default time interval between screen updates.     04
This value can be changed while the simulation is 05
running by pressing the F5 or F6 key.             06
                                                  07
dt is the time step used in the numerical         08
calculation.  Note that if dtAnim is less than dt 09
the numerical time step will be dtAnim, since the 10
dynamical variables must be calculated in order to11
update the graphs.                                12
                                                  13
At present, RK4 is the numerical method to use for14
most applications.  The Euler and RK2 methods have15
been provided solely for pedagogical use.         16
                                                  17
Additional numerical methods may be added to this 18
list in a fairly straightforward manner as        19
described in the text book that accompanies this  20
software.                                         21
